Introduction

To fit a model to monthly first hand house sales data and predict future values I choosed variables CPI based exchanged rate, CPI value of houses, interest value for bank loans for housing and the survey questions statement on current financial situation and probability of saving in next year, expectation for wage change rate and probability of buying or building a house in next year as independent variables.

Correlation and CCF

To check correlations and lagged correalations between independent variables and dependent variable I used corr function and ccf function

cors<- cor(house_sales[,c(2,3,4,5,6,7,8)], use="pairwise.complete.obs") 
corrplot.mixed(cors, tl.col="black", tl.pos = "lt")

House sales series does not show strong correlation with other series.

Some of the pairwise ccf functions show some significant lagged correlations.

CCF between house sales and exchange rate

ccf(house_sales$cpibased_exchange_rate,house_sales$sales)

Adding Lagged Variables

As lagged variables I used lag 3 house sales, lag 1 interest rate, lag 10 exchange rate and lag 11 probability of buying a house.

house_sales[,lag3:=lag(house_sales$sales,3)]
house_sales[,lag1int:=lag(interest,1)]
house_sales[,lag10exchange:=lag(cpibased_exchange_rate,10)]
house_sales[,lag11buy:=lag(prob_buy,11)]
hs_regtry=lm(sales~trend+month+year+lag3+lag1int+lag10exchange+lag11buy,data=house_sales)
summary(hs_regtry)

Conclusion

Getting the Forecast

Using the independent variables time series variables trend, months, years and lagged variables lag 3 house sales, lag 1 interest rate, lag 10 exchange rate and lag 11 probability of buying a house forecast for April 2021 is given below.

Seaonality in data is well understood but I can not identify additional variables to explain residuals. In 2020 and 2021 there are odd behaviours due to covid. There is steep decrease followed by steep increase in 2020 that my model is insufficient to explain.

#get forecast
house_sales_pred=rbind(house_sales,data.table(date=ymd("2021-04-01")),fill=T)
house_sales_pred[,trend:=1:.N]
house_sales_pred[,month:=as.character(lubridate::month(date,label=T))]
house_sales_pred[,year:=as.character(lubridate::year(date))]
house_sales_pred[,lag3:=lag(sales,3)]
house_sales_pred[,lag1int:=lag(interest,1)]
house_sales_pred[,lag10exchange:=lag(cpibased_exchange_rate,10)]
house_sales_pred[,lag11buy:=lag(prob_buy,11)]

house_sales_pred[,predicted:=predict(hs_regtry,house_sales_pred)]

print("Forecast for 04-2021 is")
## [1] "Forecast for 04-2021 is"
print(house_sales_pred[date=="2021-04-01",]$predicted)
## [1] 25012.96
ggplot(house_sales_pred ,aes(x=date)) +
  geom_line(aes(y=sales,color='real')) + 
  geom_line(aes(y=predicted,color='trend'))+labs(y="Sales", x="Date", title="House Sales") + theme_minimal(base_size=14)
